title How the Conversation Evolved (9 Phases)

start

:**1. /workflows disabled**\nUser turned off the /workflows plugin (token cost).\nQuestions: does frontier-loop still work? can loops\nrun without it? what revisions are needed?;
note right #FCF3CF: **C1** trigger question

:**2. Native substrate found**\nBackground Agent calls + completion notifications +\nSendMessage reproduce pipeline() semantics; plan v1 drafted.;
note right #FCF3CF: **C1** native substrate\n**P11** design for interruption

:**3. Ringer discovered**\nExplored ~/repos/ringer: executed checks,\nretry-with-failure-context, worktrees, model\nscoreboard, Ringside dashboard. Plan v2: ringer =\nmixed-provider substrate.;
note right #FCF3CF: **C2** adopt off the shelf\n**P1** executed checks\n**P9** isolation

:**4. Why 3 skills?**\nComparison matrix of fable-orchestration /\nfrontier-loop / ringer. Verdict: 3 layers not\ncompetitors; minimal stack = ringer + one compile skill.;
note right #FCF3CF: **C8** three layers, minimized\n**P4** split roles by price

:**5. Can ringer eat a plan?**\nNo: flat manifests, stateless specs, every task needs\nan executable check. The translation IS frontier-loop's job.;
note right #FCF3CF: **C4** wave compiler role\n**P6** checkability gate\n**P14** check craft

:**6. One brain, zero models in ringer**\nRinger is 8300 lines of stdlib Python, no LLM inside;\nthe orchestrator is the user's own Claude session.\nOne brain through the whole pipeline.;
note right #FCF3CF: **C3** ringer = muscle\n**P5** one brain orchestrates

:**7. Prior vs posterior**\nPublic benchmarks = prior for untested models; local\nscoreboard (first_try_pass_rate per task_type) =\nposterior that overrides it. Promotion ladder:\nuntested -> probation -> proven.;
note right #FCF3CF: **P7** evidence over vibes

:**8. When NOT to use it**\nCheckability is the gate; works at W=1, T=1; at W=50\nhuman gate bandwidth binds. one-minute-test is the\nfront door router.;
note right #FCF3CF: **P6** checkability gate\n**P13** gate bandwidth\n**C6** front door

:**9. Convergence**\nThree questions on three axes (scale, dependencies,\ncheckability-per-unit); routing flowchart agreed;\nplan approved for detailing.;
note right #FCF3CF: **C7** three axes\nconverge to plan

stop

